details.message: img elements must have an alt prop, either with meaningful text, or an empty string for decorative images.
Visible, non-interactive elements with click handlers must have at least one keyboard listener.
Elements with the 'button' interactive role must be tabbable.
Visible, non-interactive elements with click handlers must have at least one keyboard listener.
Avoid non-native interactive elements. If using native HTML is not possible, add an appropriate role and support for tabbing, mouse, keyboard, and touch inputs to an interactive content element.
Headings must have content and the content must be accessible by a screen reader.
<html> elements must have the lang prop.
<iframe> elements must have a unique title property.
Redundant alt attribute. Screen-readers already announce `img` tags as an image. You donâ€™t need to use the words `image`, `photo,` or `picture` (or any specified custom words) in the alt prop.
Anchors must have content and the content must be accessible by a screen reader.
A form label must be associated with a control.

The href attribute requires a valid value to be accessible. Provide a valid, navigable address as the href value. If you cannot provide a valid href, but still need the element to resemble a link, use a button and change it with appropriate styles. Learn more: https://github.com/jsx-eslint/eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y/blob/HEAD/docs/rules/anchor-is-valid.md

Do not use <marquee> elements as they can create visual accessibility issues and are deprecated.
`tabIndex` should only be declared on interactive elements.
Avoid positive integer values for tabIndex.
<html> elements must have the lang prop.
<iframe> elements must have a unique title property.
Media elements such as <audio> and <video> must have a <track> for captions.
No access key attribute allowed. Inconsistencies between keyboard shortcuts and keyboard commands used by screenreaders and keyboard-only users create a11y complications.
onBlur must be used instead of onchange, unless absolutely necessary and it causes no negative consequences for keyboard only or screen reader users.
An element that manages focus with `aria-activedescendant` must have a tabindex
